<SLUG> BC-HKN-ROY-BELFOUR-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOR ROY AND BELFOUR, THE PUCKS STOP HERE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JENNIFER FLOYD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ The thing about Stars goalie Ed Belfour and Colorado
Avalanche goalie Patrick Roy is they are just as capable of falling
on their behinds as standing on their heads.
</P>
<P>
   There is rarely a middle ground when it comes to these goalies,
and that means there isn't likely to be any two players who have a
greater impact when the Western Conference finals begin Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   With everything from tempers to rash acts in common, can you
even tell them apart?
</P>
<P>
   This goalie once told Jeremy Roenick that he couldn't hear him
because his two Stanley Cup rings were plugging his ears. He went
on to win a third later that season. ... He demanded a trade from
the only team he had ever known because his coach kept him in a
game where he had been getting shelled. ... He gets so intense
during games that he starts bobbing his head incessantly. ... He
has been credited with getting his team to this series.
</P>
<P>
   This goalie once slashed Martin Lapointe _ in his groin _
because he stepped into his crease despite it being at a crucial
point in a crucial playoff game. ... He once screamed at his
backup, Jeff Hackett, that he needed to start acting like a backup.
... He gets so antsy during games that he has to skate to the
boards during breaks in action. ... He has been credited with
getting his team to this series.
</P>
<P>
   If Roy, the one with the rings, and Belfour, the one with the
slash, seem like a matched set, eligible for the two-for-one
discount at an anger management class, that's because they are _
with one major exception.
</P>
<P>
   Roy has a reputation as being a fiery, emotional goalie who wins
Stanley Cups. Belfour has a reputation as being fiery and
emotional.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, Patrick has his status from winning Stanley Cups
and taking his teams to another level,'' Stars defenseman Darryl
Sydor said. ``That's what Eddie is trying to do right now. If you
want to win, you got to beat one of the best and Patrick is one of
the best.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is a lot of talk about Patrick, but don't overlook our
goalie. He is playing really well.''
</P>
<P>
   Numbers support Belfour.
</P>
<P>
   He ranks second in goals-against averqgN
</P>
</TEXT>
