<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times has two staff writers, Kevin Sack and David
Firestone, covering the school shooting in George. Here is a
preliminary lineup of stories:
</P>
<P>
   GA-SCHOOL-SHOOTING (Conyers, Ga.) _ A student opened fire at a
suburban Atlanta high school early Thursday, injuring six other
students a month to the day after the Colorado school massacre,
police said. The police said none of the injuries were
life-threatening and the shooter had been taken into custody.
Identified as a sophomore boy at Heritage High School here, the
shooter was taken into custody within 10 minutes, police said.
Witnesses said he carried at least two weapons, a pump-style
shotgun and a revolver. Some reports said he tried to put the
revolver in his mouth before authorities captured him.
</P>
<P>
   GA-SCHOOL-SHOOTER (Conyers, Ga.) _ What we know about the
student who fired the shots.
</P>
<P>
   We are considering a feature on the copycat phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
   And this related story:
</P>
<P>
   COLO-SCHOOL-CLINTON (Littleton, Co.) _ President Clinton visits
the town that experienced the last school massacre. Plus an update
on the Columbine High School investigation. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, our partner  &UR; Cox News Service &LR; , through its paper
 &UR; The Atlanta Journal-Constitution &LR; , has moved a spot lede, with
others to come.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-SHOOTING20-COX (Conyers, Ga.) _ Six students at a
suburban Atlanta high school were injured today in a shooting and
authorities had a suspect in custody, officials said. None of the
injuries was believed to be life-threatening, said Bonnie Knight, a
spokeswoman for Rockdale County schools. The shooting came exactly
a month after the April 20 slaughter at Columbine High School in
Littleton, Colo., where two students killed 13 people before taking
their own lives. By Mike Morris.
</P>
