<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Getaway festivals
 &HT;    By paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Savannah _ Savannah Sojourn, the Third Annual Georgia
Historical Society Antiques Show and Sale, is Friday through Sunday
at the Savannah Civic Center. Friday's events include a home and
garden tour, followed by an afternoon seminar ``Jewelry in
America'' by Riya Takaya of Christie's of New York. The show and
sale is Saturday and Sunday. 912-232-3411.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Augusta _ The Morris Museum of Art presents ``Robert
Stackhouse: Major Works 1969-1999,'' the first retrospective for
the painter and sculptor, Thursday through Aug. 22. Opening
symposium and reception 4-7:30 p.m. Thursday features speakers
including Stackhouse, William Christenberry, Richard Belger, Myra
Morgan and J. Richard Gruber. 706-724-7501.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Macon _ ``Such Beautiful Things _ Highlights from the Hay
Porcelain Collection'' will be exhibited through July 18 at the
1859 Hay House, an 1859 Italianate Revival mansion that is now a
house museum. 912-742-8155.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Hiawassee _ The Rhododendron Festival Friday through Sunday
and May 28-30 features arts and crafts, clogging and country music.
Loretta Lynn and the Lynns will perform May 29. 706-896-4191.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Atlanta _ The Container Store is hosting free ``Organized
Traveler'' workshops that include advice on packing and travel
checklists at the following store locations: 120 Perimeter Center,
770-351-0065 (1 and 3 p.m. Saturday and June 5, and 3 p.m. Sunday
and June 6); 3255 Peachtree Road N.E., 404-261-4776 (1 and 3 p.m.
June 12, and 3 p.m. June 13).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Cherokee, N.C. _ Harrah's Cherokee Casino presents comedian
Bill Cosby for two shows Thursday. Tickets are $36;
1-800-427-7247.0
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Memphis _ The monthlong Memphis in May International Festival
includes World Championship Barbecue Cooking Contest
(Thursday-Saturday) and the Sunset Symphony with fireworks display
(May 29). Events held in Tom Lee Park. 901-525-4611 or www
</P>
<P>
   .memphisinmay.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Rugby, Tenn. _ The 25th annual Historic Rugby Festival of
British and Appalachian Culture Saturday and Sunday features music
from the British Isles and Appalachian cultures, arts and crafts,
historic tours and daily concerts by Scottish singer Jean Redpath.
423-628-2441 or www.historicrugby
</P>
<P>
   .org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Meridian, Miss. _ The Jimmie Rodgers Memorial Festival, a
tribute to the ``father of country music,'' is Saturday through May
29. 601-483-5763 or www.jimmierodgers
</P>
<P>
   .com/Main/Festival/festival.html.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Natchez, Miss. _ The Natchez Opera Festival through May 29
showcases opera stars in seven productions, including ``Carousel''
and ``Don Giovanni,'' along with plantation recitals and
instrumental concerts. 601-442-7464 or www2.bkbank.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Richmond _ The Virginia Museum of Fine Arts will open ``The
Splendors of Egypt'' exhibit on Tuesday. The exhibition presents a
panoramic view of one of the world's oldest and most sophisticated
civilizations, with more than 200 masterpieces, some at least 5,000
years old. Through Nov. 28. 804-367-0878 or www.vmfa.state
</P>
<P>
   .va.us.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Union Grove, N.C. _ The 75th annual Ole Time Fiddler's &AMP;
Bluegrass Festival is May 28-30 at Fiddler's Grove Campground. Acts
include the Cockman Family of North Carolina and the Kruger
Brothers from Switzerland. 704-539-4417.
</P>
<P>
   Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
