   HOLOCAUST-STLOUIS (Undated) _ Sixty years ago the St. Louis
sailed from Hamburg with 930 European Jews on board seeking safe
haven in America. Thwarted, they were eventually forced back to
Europe where more than 220 died in the Holocaust. Now the Holocaust
Memorial Museum is commemorating the voyage. By Irene Sege. (2
takes; includes missing passengers list; a and i coding) PHOTOS (2)
