   TV-CLEOPATRA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In four hours over two days and at a cost of more than
$30 million, ``Cleopatra'' manages to titillate viewers but hardly
illuminate the portrait of the queen of Egypt, whose life story is
complex and fascinating, and so deserving of a more definitive,
respectful telling. TV Critic Ken Parish Perkins reviews the ABC
miniseries. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-PERKINS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Saturday's ``A Lesson Before Dying'' is based on
Ernest J. Gaines' captivating novel about death and despair,
courage and triumph, dreams and inner-self preservation. TV Critic
Ken Parish Perkins reviews the HBO film. By KEN PARISH PERKINS.
Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CAPSHAW-LOVE LETTER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Actress Kate Capshaw loved Cathleen Schine's novel
``The Love Letter'' so much, she decided to turn it into a movie.
Little did she know that the small film would be scheduled against
``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace.'' The actress _ a Fort
Worth native _ talks about her David-vs.- Goliath effort and about
her father's love for Texas. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LOVE LETTER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ A movie couldn't be filled with a nicer group of
people than the characters in this film adaptation of Cathleen
Schine's novel, ``The Love Letter.'' It follows the waves caused
when an anonymous love letter, filled with ever so slightly
lavender prose, makes its way through a small New England town. By
ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-TREKKIES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Leave it to Data to sum up the appeal of ``Trekkies,''
Roger Nygard's bemused and amusing documentary about ``Star Trek''
fans. Well, not Data, really, but Brent Spiner, who played the
wannabe-human android on ``Star Trek: The Next Generation.'' Spiner
readily acknowledges the peculiarity of the most passionate ``Star
Trek'' aficionados _ but then asks, aren't we all peculiar in some
way? By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-THREE SEASONS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Three Seasons'' is a beautifully melancholy new film
from 26-year-old Vietnamese-American director Tony Bui. It is
strongly literary but distinctly cinematic, an astute synching of
words, pictures and sounds. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
