<HEADLINE>
GLOSSARY OF TERMS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Biotechnology _ Harnessing and altering organic molecules, cells
or living organisms to produce products such as drugs or other
useful organisms.
</P>
<P>
   Molecular biology _ The study of life at the molecular level.
</P>
<P>
   DNA _ Deoxyribonucleic acid, a molecule made up billions of
differing sequences of four base units carrying the genetic
information of most living creatures.
</P>
<P>
   Gene _ Genes govern what cells do, which determines what the
creatures do.
</P>
<P>
   Protein _ The direct product of genes. Proteins do the work.
</P>
<P>
   Chromosome _ The structure in the cell that contains DNA and
genes.
</P>
<P>
   Genome _ The total genetic code of a living creature.
</P>
<P>
   Technology transfer _ Typically, the transfer of a scientific
discovery from the university or government laboratory to industry
for commercial application.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
