<P>
   AIRTRAN-SHAREHOLDERS _ ATLANTA _ AirTran shareholders are
meeting in Atlanta today. Last month, the carrier regained some
financial altitude in the first quarter, posting a modest profit
that beat analysts' forecasts. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WEB-MD _ WebMD Inc. announces plans to merge with Healtheon, a
deal that puts the combined company's market value at $16 billion.
Healtheon and WebMD said the combined company will be headquartered
in Atlanta, with technology headquartees in Santa Clara, Calif. The
company will have a total of 10 offices around the country.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   IXL-IPO _ The latest Internet IPO should happen this week, when
iXL Enterprises goes public. Opening price is expected to be
$10-$12, but should rise quickly, although analysts say the company
is little more than a random collection of Internet services. This
is the company run by Bert Ellis, who gave $1 million to Ga. Tech
to start an e-commerce center recently. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
