<P>
   CONGRESS-GUNS (Washington) _ The Senate expected to pass the
juvenile justice bill, with gun-control measures attached,
including one on gun shows in which the vote was 50-50 with Vice
President Al Gore casting the tie-breaking vote in favor. The final
vote is expected to be late. By Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   GA-SCHOOL-SHOOTING (Conyers, Ga.) _ A student opened fire at a
suburban Atlanta high school early Thursday, injuring six other
students a month to the day after the Colorado school massacre,
police said. The police said none of the injuries were
life-threatening and the shooter had been taken into custody. By
Kevin Sack.
