   KOSOVO-ATTACK (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ NATO bombed a hospital
Thursday morning. At least four people were killed and dozens
wounded, including medical staff and two women who suffered cuts
and facial injuries from broken glass while they were giving birth.
By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BELGRADE (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ War fatigue is growing
here, prompting a circumspect political debate and encouraging the
splintered opposition to think about what Yugoslavia could look
like after the war, and even after President Slobodan Milosevic.
But these stirrings remain faint. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   VITAMIN-PRICE-FIXING (Washington) _ Federal prosecutors
announced that they had shattered one of the worst cartels ever
discovered, one that controlled the prices and distributions of
vitamins used for products in every refrigerator and kitchen
cabinet in America, from morning supplementals to enriched milk and
orange juice, fortified breakfast cereals, breads and meats. By
David Barboza and Stephen Labaton.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   NY-LOUIMA-COPS (New York) _ The so-called blue wall of silence
is crashing down on Justin Volpe. One after another, his fellow
police officers have paraded to the witness stand and offered vivid
details in support of an awful allegation _ that Volpe, lost in a
sadistic rage, rammed a stick into the rectum of a handcuffed
Haitian immigrant. By David Barstow.
</P>
