<P>
   REFUGEES-SEATTLE (Seattle) _ The first family of Kosovar
refugees to be resettled in Washington arrives Thursday night and
will be making a temporary home with Karlene Kennedy, of Seattle,
before moving into their own apartment. The family is the first of
as many as 500 ethnic Albanian refugees who are expected to be
resettled in Western Washington in the coming weeks.
