<P>
   CHURCH-ANNIVERSARY (Seattle) _ Above the altar at Japanese
Baptist Church of Seattle, near a row of windows lighting the
six-sided sanctuary, hangs a framed piece of Japanese calligraphy.
``Kamiwa ai nari,'' the words read. Translated, the expression is
simple yet profound: ``God is love.'' That message has carried the
congregation over the past century, through waves of immigration,
periods of war and changes in demographics. The red brick church
celebrates its 100th anniversary beginning Friday.
