<P>
   (NYT15) NEW YORK -- May 20, 1999 -- MET-APPOINT, 5-20 -- Paul
Montrone, the new president of the Metropolitan Opera, during a
recent interview. Montrone was elected president and chief
executive officer of the Metropolitan Opera Association at its
annual meeting on Thursday. A native of Scranton, Pa., Montrone
joined the Met's advisory board in 1986 and its managing board in
1991. He is chief executive officer of Fisher Scientific
International Inc., which supplies products and services to
research and clinical laboratories. (Chester Higgins Jr./New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) ISTANBUL, Turkey -- May 20, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY
23 -- TURKEY-BLUES-RADIO, 05-20 -- Serter Alkaya, an Acik Radyo
engineer in Istanbul, monitors the sound while Stephen Kinzer, a
blues D.J., tapes his program. Istanbul is one of the world's most
vibrant and sophisticated cities, and many people here are tuned in
to world culture just as completely as their cousins in London or
Paris. (Staton Winter/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) NEW YORK -- May 20, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY 23 --
RICHARD-NELSON-THEATER, 05-20 -- ``Goodnight Children Everywhere,''
Richard Nelson' s latest play, is opening Off Broadway on Wednesday
at Playwrights Horizons. It marks the first time that Nelson has
written a work wholly about the English and set in England. (Sara
Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- May 20, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY 23 --
