of time. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) JERUSALEM -- May 20, 1999 -- ISRAEL-SHAS, 5-20 -- Arieh
Deri, leader of the Shas Party, during a rally near a portrait of
Rabbis Ovadia Yossef, right, and Khadour, the spiritual advisors
for the party. Shas, Israel's religious party, went from 10 seats
in the Israeli parliament to 17 in elections earlier this week. The
increase makes Shas the third biggest bloc in parliament after
Labor and Likud. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) NORTH ADAMS, Mass. -- May 20, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY
23 -- VIDEO-ARTIST, 05-20 -- Tony Oursler working on a video
project with Tom Hines as a devil and Lilah Freedland as an angel.
Oursler's new work, titled ``Optics'' was commissioned by the
Williams College Museum of Art in nearby Williamstown and the
Massachusetts Museum of Contemporary Art, called colloquially Mass
MOCA. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) WASHINGTON -- May 20, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY 23 --
ECHAVESTE-COX-2, 5-20 -- Maria Echaveste, the White House deputy
