<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the additional
story for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Friday, May 21, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Veronica Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   PASTOR-MOOREHEAD (REDMOND, Wash.) _ New testimony gives strong
support to sexual misconduct allegations against the Rev. Bob
Moorehead, who resigned last year from Overlake Christian Church,
leaders of the Redmond, Wash., congregation said Thursday. Church
elders have heard from multiple witnesses to at least some of the
allegations leveled against Moorehead, according to a letter sent
to members of Washington's largest church. Last May, the elders
dismissed allegations of sexual misconduct against Moorehead by 17
men because they said the incidents couldn't be substantiated by
eyewitnesses.
</P>
<P>
   By John Iwasaki. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
