climate for makers of antipollution equipment, says Jeffrey Smith,
executive director of the Institute of Clean Air Companies. Smith's
organization represents pollution control equipment makers and made
several comments on the court ruling made recently which tossed out
new EPA smog rules. (Justin Lane/New York Times Photo)
