SAFRICA-CELLPHONES, 5-20 -- Naomi Shaku, who lives in a government
developed housing area east of Johannesburg called Ebony Park, says
she would be helpless without her cell phone. Public phones in
South Africa are sparse and do not always function. Besides, many
poorer areas like Ebony Park simply are not served by telephone
lines. (W.A. Bridges Jr./Cox News Service) LITE
