<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, MAY 21
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-WISDOM-NYT (moved on Saturday, May 15)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of John Minor Wisdom, sent by the New York Times
News Service on Saturday, May 15, misidentified the unsuccessful
Supreme Court nomination he opposed in 1969. It was not that of
Judge Clement F. Haynsworth Jr. but that of Judge G. Harrold
Carswell, who was nominated next.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-TUNA-RISK-NYT (moved on Monday, May 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 10,
about mercury levels in canned tuna misstated the Food and Drug
Administration's safe limit for human consumption of methyl
mercury. It is 1.0 parts per million, not 0.1 part.
</P>
