<P>
   (NYT30) WASHINGTON -- May 20, 1999 -- MCCAIN-CLINTON, 5-20 --
Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., outlines his views on foreign affairs
during a speech at the National Press Club on Thursday. McCain,
exploring a presidential candidacy in 2000, was harshly critical of
President Clinton on issues from Kosovo to the Middle East to
international trade. (Justin Lane/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) GLEN COVE, New York -- May 20, 1999 -- NY-SUBURBS-IMMIG,
5-20 -- Family members and friends gather in room to look at some
television. Behind split-level shutters, vinyl siding and drawn
curtains in nearly every town and village on New York's Long
Island, tens of thousands of legal and illegal immigrants from
Central America and Mexico are jammed into subdivided houses and
partitioned apartments, biding their time in invisible suburban
slums. (Vic DeLucia/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
