<HEADLINE>
CLAYTON READY TO RETURN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOHNNY PAUL 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ Rangers shortstop Royce Clayton experienced
no difficulties during his two-game medical rehabilitation
assignment and should be reinstated from the 15-day disabled list
before tonight's game against the Orioles in Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   Clayton (torn muscle, right shoulder) played nine innings
Tuesday and Wednesday for Triple-A Oklahoma and went 1-for-7 with
three walks and one run batted in during two games at Tucson.
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers plan to option shortstop Kelly Dransfeldt to
Oklahoma to make room on the 25-man roster for Clayton, who went on
the disabled list May 1. Clayton hit only .150 (9-for-60) during 19
games before the injury forced him to the disabled list. BACK TO
BALTIMORE Rangers designated hitter Rafael Palmeiro will make his
first appearance in Oriole Park at Camden Yards tonight after
leaving the Orioles this winter as a free agent.
</P>
<P>
   Palmeiro will return hitting .377 with 11 home runs and 36 runs
batted in.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to concentrate on what to do, not against who,''
said Palmeiro, who Wednesday had the 20th two-homer game of his
career.
</P>
<P>
   Palmeiro hit .500 (13-for-26) with five home runs and 13 RBI
during the Rangers' recent seven-game homestand and called the
streak ``probably one of my best, if not my best.'' CLARK TO MISS
SERIES Orioles first baseman Will Clark (fracture, left thumb)
likely will not be reinstated from the 15-day disabled list until
after the Rangers leave Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   The Orioles sent Clark to their extended spring training program
in Sarasota, Fla., yesterday and plan for him to play there today
and tomorrow. The Orioles will evaluate Clark's progress Sunday and
determine a course of action. Clark played for the Rangers from
1994-98. PACKAGE TICKET PLAN The Rangers yesterday announced a
15-game, season-ticket miniplan involving The Ballpark in
Arlington's club-level seats.
</P>
<P>
   ``Power in the Park'' includes 15 scheduled games during July,
August and September and an option for postseason tickets. The plan
also includes discount coupons for merchandise, food and beverages
at The Ballpark's Diamond Club and a voucher for two free
upper-level tickets.
</P>
<P>
   Call the Rangers' ticket office at (817) 273-5100 for more
information. BRIEFLY Outfielder Mike Simms went 0-for-3 with a walk
as Triple-A Oklahoma's designated hitter Wednesday while on his
second medical rehabilitation assignment. Simms (torn tendon, left
Achilles) went on the 15-day disabled list before the season began
and his return remains unclear.
</P>
<P>
   Left fielder Rusty Greer will take an eight-game hitting steak
to Oriole Park at Camden Yards. Greer and second baseman Mark
McLemore share the Rangers' longest hitting streak of the season at
10 games. / nn
</P>
</TEXT>
